kdebase-workspace (4:4.0.73+svn808019-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * New upstream development snapshot:
    - The latest upstream commit is r808019 by pino
    - Date: Thu May 15 12:25:39 2008 UTC

  * Resolved bugs:
    - kdm password field is again reachable without mouse click when using
      Debian kdm theme. (Closes: #478666)
  * NetworkManager enabled.

  +++ Changes by Modestas Vainius:

  * Update install files.
  * Refresh patches (adopt to upstream changes):
    * 10_kdm_no_custom
    * 97_fix_target_link_libraries

  +++ Changes by Armin Berres:

  * Raise libkwineffects1 shlibs version in debian/rules.
  * Patch kdm to start the X server with a black background instead of the
    default checkerboard.
  * Don't install /usr/lib/libkwinnvidiahack.so. No one is supposed to link
    against libkwinnvidiahack. Make kdebase-workspace-dev depend on
    libkdecorations4 and libkwineffects1 instead of kde-window-manager now
    that kde-window-manager contains nothing one can link against.
  * Move shared libraries to kdebase-workspace-libs4+5 so we can raise the
    soname if needed. Update kdebase-workspace-dev dependencies accordingly.

  +++ Changes by Fathi Boudra:

  * Add 20 patch to use DejaVu font as default font.
  * Add 21 patch to disable blend title bar.
  * Fix 97_fix_target_link_libraries patch:
    proper libplasma target link libraries.
  * Add libqt4-opengl-dev build dependency since Qt4 split.

